# Performance Conventions

## Images — Always `next/image`

Never use a plain `<img>` tag. Always use `next/image` for automatic optimization (WebP/AVIF, lazy loading, size optimization).

```jsx
import Image from 'next/image'

// ✅ Fixed dimensions
<Image
  src="/images/products/transformer.jpg"
  alt="Smart Transformer X200"
  width={600}
  height={400}
  className="rounded-lg object-cover"
/>

// ✅ Fill parent container (for background-style images)
<div className="relative h-64">
  <Image
    src="/images/hero-bg.jpg"
    alt="Smart grid infrastructure"
    fill
    className="object-cover object-center"
    priority    // ← add priority on above-the-fold images
  />
</div>
```

Rules:

- Add `priority` prop on hero/above-the-fold images to preload them
- Use `fill` + `className="object-cover"` for full-bleed images
- Always provide a descriptive `alt` string — never empty except for decorative images
- All images live in `public/images/` and are referenced from `/images/...`

---

## Static Generation — `generateStaticParams`

Dynamic pages (`[slug]`) must be pre-rendered at build time using `generateStaticParams`.

```jsx
// ✅ Pre-renders all product pages at build time
export async function generateStaticParams() {
  const products = await getProducts();
  return products.map((p) => ({ slug: p.slug }));
}
```

If a page could have thousands of items, use `dynamicParams = false` to 404 unknown slugs:

```js
export const dynamicParams = false;
```

---

## Fonts — `next/font`

Load fonts with `next/font` in the root layout. Never use a `<link>` tag in `<head>` for fonts.

```jsx
// app/layout.jsx
import { Inter, Sora } from "next/font/google";

const sora = Sora({
  subsets: ["latin"],
  variable: "--font-sora",
  display: "swap",
});

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className={sora.variable}>
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

