## Metadata — Every Page

Every `page.jsx` must export metadata for SEO:

```jsx
// Static metadata
export const metadata = {
  title: "Products | VHT",
  description: "Browse our full range of VHT products.",
  openGraph: {
    title: "Products | VHT",
    description: "Browse our full range of VHT products.",
    images: ["/images/og/products.jpg"],
  },
};

// Dynamic metadata
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
  const product = await getProductBySlug(params.slug);
  return {
    title: `${product.name} | VHT`,
    description: product.summary,
  };
}
```

---

## Code Splitting — Lazy Load Heavy Sections

For large below-the-fold sections with heavy JS (e.g., interactive maps, charts), use `next/dynamic`:

```jsx
import dynamic from "next/dynamic";

const HeavyInteractiveChart = dynamic(
  () => import("@/features/solutions/HeavyChart"),
  {
    loading: () => (
      <div className="h-64 animate-pulse bg-slate-800 rounded-lg" />
    ),
    ssr: false, // only if component uses browser APIs
  },
);
```

